ecpaControlTable.name: ecpaControlTable
ecpaControlTable.description: A list of entries for the control of Etherjack Connection Performance Analyzer Streams. Upto 12 ECPA streams can be configured per test head; 3 ECPA streams can be simultaneously executed.

ecpaControlEntry.name: ecpaControlEntry
ecpaControlEntry.description: A conceptual row in the ecpaControlTable.

ecpaControlIndex.name: ecpaControlIndex
ecpaControlIndex.description: An arbitrary integer index value used to uniquely identify this Etherjack Connection Performance Analyzer Control Test head. There is only one test head per card.

ecpaControlSourcePort.name: ecpaControlSourcePort
ecpaControlSourcePort.description: Pointer to the Access or Network Port on which the ECPA test will be started within a card.

ecpaControlTestType.name: ecpaControlTestType
ecpaControlTestType.description: The type of ECPA test to be performed. When 'duration' test is specified, ECPA test is run for 'ecpaControlDuration' time. When 'numFrames' test is specified, ECPA test is run for 'ecpaControlNumFrames', when 'continous' test is specified, ECPA test is run until an explicit 'ecpaControlAction' of 'stop' of received.

ecpaControlNumFrames.name: ecpaControlNumFrames
ecpaControlNumFrames.description: This object enables specification of the number of frames for traffic generation. Traffic Generation will be completed after the specified number of frames are transmitted.

ecpaControlDuration.name: ecpaControlDuration
ecpaControlDuration.description: This object enables specification of the time in seconds for traffic generation. Traffic Generation will be stopped after the specified time interval is exhausted.

ecpaControlInjectorDirection.name: ecpaControlInjectorDirection
ecpaControlInjectorDirection.description: This object enables specification of the direction of traffic generation. This value must be specified if the interface is used for traffic generation. Both of ecpaControlInjectorDirection and ecpaControlMonitorDirection must be specified.

ecpaControlMonitorDirection.name: ecpaControlMonitorDirection
ecpaControlMonitorDirection.description: This object enables specification of the direction of receival of generated traffic. This value must be specified if the interface is used for receiving/monitoring generated traffic. Both of ecpaControlInjectorDirection and ecpaControlMonitorDirection must be specified.

ecpaControlStream1.name: ecpaControlStream1
ecpaControlStream1.description: This object specifies which stream should be included in the ECPA execution. Value of 0 indicates that no streams is selected by ecpaControlStream1. Non 0 value indicates the selected ECPA stream.

ecpaControlStream2.name: ecpaControlStream2
ecpaControlStream2.description: This object specifies which stream should be included in the ECPA execution. Value of 0 indicates that no streams is selected by ecpaControlStream2. Non 0 value indicates the selected ECPA stream.

ecpaControlStream3.name: ecpaControlStream3
ecpaControlStream3.description: This object specifies which stream should be included in the ECPA execution. Value of 0 indicates that no streams is selected by ecpaControlStream3. Non 0 value indicates the selected ECPA stream.

ecpaControlAction.name: ecpaControlAction
ecpaControlAction.description: This object enables starting/stopping of traffic generation as well as resetting of monitored streams. This object may not be specified at configuration creation time - in this case it will take the value of `none'. This allows manager to explicitly control the start and stop of traffic generation/monitoring activity. Value of `stop' is invalid if the activity is specified but not started. Value of `start' is valid during creation time, as well as when activity is already stopped. Specification of `reset' resets the specified streams to default values, as well as clears the control specification. Get on this variable gives the most recent SNMP set specification.

ecpaControlTestStatus.name: ecpaControlTestStatus
ecpaControlTestStatus.description: This object reflects the current status of test set configuration entry. Upon creation, the status has a value of `initial'; the status changes to `in-progress' upon ecpaControlAction indicating `start'; the status changes to `completed' upon ecpaControlAction indicating stop, as well as when the specified test generation completes autonomously upon completion of number of frames or completion of specified time interval.

ecpaControlStorageType.name: ecpaControlStorageType
ecpaControlStorageType.description: The type of storage configured for this entry.

ecpaControlRowStatus.name: ecpaControlRowStatus
ecpaControlRowStatus.description: The status of this row. An entry MUST NOT exist in the active state unless all objects in the entry have an appropriate value, as described in the description clause for each writable object. The values of ecpaControlRowStatus supported are createAndGo(4) and destroy(6). All mandatory attributes must be specified in a single SNMP SET request with ecpaControlRowStatus value as createAndGo(4). Upon successful row creation, this object has a value of active(1). The ecpaControlRowStatus object may be modified if the associated instance of this object is equal to active(1).

ecpaConfigStreamIndex.name: ecpaConfigStreamIndex

ecpaConfigStreamFrameSize.name: ecpaConfigStreamFrameSize
ecpaConfigStreamFrameSize.description: This object enables specification of fixed length frame size in bytes for traffic generation. If not specified, default value of 64 bytes is used. CM Aggregation Product limits the upper range value to 9600.

ecpaConfigStreamRate.name: ecpaConfigStreamRate
ecpaConfigStreamRate.description: The object enables specification of the traffic generation rate.

ecpaConfigStreamPayloadType.name: ecpaConfigStreamPayloadType
ecpaConfigStreamPayloadType.description: This object enables specification of type of payload to generate `fixed' type indicates a generation pattern of 5A, A5, 5A, A5 bytes. `random' type indicates traffic generation with pseudo-random pattern.

ecpaConfigStreamSignature.name: ecpaConfigStreamSignature
ecpaConfigStreamSignature.description: Indicates an 8-byte signature specified by the user in hexadecimal or ASCII format. This signature is currently used by the FSP150Mx products for test frame recognition and will be appended directly after the ECPA Signature in the test frame and be 4-byte aligned. This will allow the F3 ECPA feature to interoperate with the existing FSP150Mx products. Hexadecimal signature must be prefixed with 0x/0X.

esaProbeAssocSchedGroup.description: This object points to the probe's associated Scheduled Group. Initially, when the probe is not associated with a Group, this object's value is set to {0.0}.

esaProbeDirection.name: esaProbeDirection
esaProbeDirection.description: This object allows to specify the direction of Probe traffic generation.

esaProbeProtocol.name: esaProbeProtocol
esaProbeProtocol.description: Protocol to be used in ESA Probe messages. 'icmpTimestamp', 'icmpEcho', 'udpEcho' protocols support layer-3 ethernet service assurance. If the remote reflector is an ADVA equipment based on CM family of products, one-way loss measurement, one-way delay measurement, round-trip delay measurement and one-way jitter measurements are computed. Else, only round-trip delay measurements are applicable. 'y1731' protocol can be used for layer-2 ethernet service assurance. One-way loss measurement, one-way and round-trip delay measurement, and one-way jitter measurements are available for this protocol. 'y1731-slm-slr' protocol can be used for layer-2 ethernet service assurance using Synthetic Loss Measurement messages. One-way loss measurement, one-way and round-trip delay measurement, and one-way jitter measurements are available for this protocol.

esaProbeSrcIpAddress.name: esaProbeSrcIpAddress
esaProbeSrcIpAddress.description: Variable that allows specification of the Probe's source IP Address. This IP Address is used in the IP header of the ESA Probe generated packets, as source address. NOTE: This attribute is not applicable to Y.1731 probes.

esaProbeSrcSubnetMask.name: esaProbeSrcSubnetMask
esaProbeSrcSubnetMask.description: Variable that allows specification of the Probe's source IP Subnet Mask. NOTE: This attribute is not applicable to Y.1731 probes.

esaProbeDestIpAddress.name: esaProbeDestIpAddress
esaProbeDestIpAddress.description: Variable that allows specification of the Reflector's destination IP Address. This IP Address is used in the IP header of the ESA Probe generated packets, as destination address. NOTE: This attribute is not applicable to Y.1731 probes.

esaProbeSrcMep.name: esaProbeSrcMep
esaProbeSrcMep.description: This attribute is applicable only for Y.1731 probes. It identifies the source MEP that initiates the Y.1731 LMMs and DMMs.

esaProbeDestMepType.name: esaProbeDestMepType
esaProbeDestMepType.description: This attribute is applicable only for Y.1731 probes. This indicates if the destination MEP is specified using the MEP ID object esaProbeDestMepId.

esaProbeDestMepMacAddr.name: esaProbeDestMepMacAddr
esaProbeDestMepMacAddr.description: This attribute is applicable only for Y.1731 probes. It identifies the destination MEP that responds to the LMMs and DMMs. This MAC address will be the destination MAC address for LMM and DMM frames if esaProbeY1731DestMepType is 'macaddress'. If CC protocol is not enabled between source and destination MEP then this is the only choice to identify the remote MEP.

esaProbeDestMepId.name: esaProbeDestMepId
esaProbeDestMepId.description: This attribute is applicable only for Y.1731 probes. It identifies the destination MEP that responds to the LMMs and DMMs. The MAC address of this RMEP ID from RMEP database will be the destination MAC address for LMM and DMM. This value is used only if the esaProbeY1731DestMepType is 'mepid'. CC protocol must be enabled between source and destination MEP if the RMEP ID is used to identify the Remote MEP.

esaProbeVlanTagEnabled.name: esaProbeVlanTagEnabled
esaProbeVlanTagEnabled.description: Ability to specify whether or not to use VLAN tagged or untagged ESA traffic generation on the Probe. NOTE: This attribute is not applicable to Y.1731 probes.

esaProbeVlanTagEtherType.name: esaProbeVlanTagEtherType
esaProbeVlanTagEtherType.description: This variable allows the user to specify the monitored service's VLAN tag Ether Type. Valid if 'esaProbeVlanTagEnabled' is specified as TRUE. NOTE: This attribute is not applicable to Y.1731 probes.

esaProbeVlanId.name: esaProbeVlanId
esaProbeVlanId.description: This variable allows the user to specify the monitored service's VLAN tag. Valid if 'esaProbeVlanTagEnabled' is specified as TRUE. NOTE: This attribute is not applicable to Y.1731 probes.

esaProbeVlanPrio.name: esaProbeVlanPrio
esaProbeVlanPrio.description: This variable allows the user to specify the monitored service's VLAN priority. Valid if 'esaProbeVlanTagEnabled' is specified as TRUE. NOTE: This attribute is not applicable to Y.1731 probes.

esaProbeInnerVlanTagEnabled.name: esaProbeInnerVlanTagEnabled
esaProbeInnerVlanTagEnabled.description: Ability to specify whether or not to use Inner VLAN tag. NOTE: This attribute is not applicable to Y.1731 probes.

esaProbeInnerVlanTagEtherType.name: esaProbeInnerVlanTagEtherType
esaProbeInnerVlanTagEtherType.description: This variable allows the user to specify the monitored service's Inner VLAN tag Ether Type. Valid if 'esaProbeInnerVlanTagEnabled' is specified as TRUE. NOTE: This attribute is not applicable to Y.1731 probes.

esaProbeInnerVlanId.name: esaProbeInnerVlanId
esaProbeInnerVlanId.description: This variable allows the user to specify the monitored service's Inner VLAN tag. Valid if 'esaProbeInnerVlanTagEnabled' is specified as TRUE. NOTE: This attribute is not applicable to Y.1731 probes.

esaProbeInnerVlanPrio.name: esaProbeInnerVlanPrio
esaProbeInnerVlanPrio.description: This variable allows the user to specify the monitored service's Inner VLAN priority. Valid if 'esaProbeInnerVlanTagEnabled' is specified as TRUE. NOTE: This attribute is not applicable to Y.1731 probes.

esaProbeIpPrioMapMode.name: esaProbeIpPrioMapMode
esaProbeIpPrioMapMode.description: This object enables specification of Priority Mapping Mode for the ESA Probe. NOTE: This attribute is not applicable to Y.1731 probes.

esaProbeIpPriority.name: esaProbeIpPriority
esaProbeIpPriority.description: This object enables specification of Priority Value for esaProbePrioMapMode as priomap-tos,priomap-dscp. NOTE: This attribute is not applicable to Y.1731 probes.

esaProbePktsPerSample.name: esaProbePktsPerSample
esaProbePktsPerSample.description: This object enables specification of number of packets within a sample run for ESA traffic generation. A non-zero value must be specified. NOTE: This attribute is not applicable to Y.1731 probes.

esaProbePktSize.name: esaProbePktSize
esaProbePktSize.description: This object enables specification of fixed length frame size in bytes for ESA traffic generation. If not specified, default value of 104 bytes is used. NOTE: This attribute is not available to Y.1731 probes.

esaProbeInterPktGap.name: esaProbeInterPktGap
esaProbeInterPktGap.description: This object enables specification of interval in milliseconds between packet generation. A non-zero value must be specified. NOTE: This attribute is not applicable to Y.1731 probes.

esaProbePktDeadInterval.name: esaProbePktDeadInterval
esaProbePktDeadInterval.description: This object enables specification of the dead interval in seconds after 'esaProbePktsPerSample' have been generated within the sample. This allows for settling time of the ESA traffic. A non-zero value must be specified. NOTE: This attribute is not applicable to Y.1731 probes.

esaProbeResponseTimeout.name: esaProbeResponseTimeout
esaProbeResponseTimeout.description: This object allows specification of the timeout value to determine lost packets. Time specified in seconds. NOTE: This attribute is not applicable to Y.1731 probes. This object is applicable to Layer 3 and SLM/SLR Probes.

esaProbeY1731DmmPktSize.name: esaProbeY1731DmmPktSize
esaProbeY1731DmmPktSize.description: This object is only applicable to Y.1731 probes. This object enables specification of the TLV size for Delay Measurement Frames (DMMs). Value of 0 is a read-only value when the Probe protocol is not y1731. GE206 Release 4.4.x supports 2000 bytes

esaProbeY1731LmmInterval.name: esaProbeY1731LmmInterval
esaProbeY1731LmmInterval.description: LMM frame transmission period. For Loss Measurement Frames, only interval-1sec is supported. This attribute is only applicable to Y.1731 probes.

esaProbeY1731DmmInterval.name: esaProbeY1731DmmInterval
esaProbeY1731DmmInterval.description: DMM frame transmission period. This attribute is only applicable to Y.1731 probes.

esaProbeHistoryBins.name: esaProbeHistoryBins
esaProbeHistoryBins.description: This object allows specification of number of history bins. This is the total history data that will be maintained for an ESA Probe run, at any instance.

esaProbeHistoryInterval.name: esaProbeHistoryInterval
esaProbeHistoryInterval.description: This object allows specification of the history interval period.

esaProbeDistHistoryBins.name: esaProbeDistHistoryBins
esaProbeDistHistoryBins.description: This object allows specification of number of distribution history bins. This is the total history distribution data that will be maintained for an ESA Probe run, at any instance.

esaProbeDistHistoryInterval.name: esaProbeDistHistoryInterval
esaProbeDistHistoryInterval.description: This object allows specification of the history distribution interval period.

esaProbeCreationTime.name: esaProbeCreationTime
esaProbeCreationTime.description: This object provides the creation time of the ESA Probe.

esaProbeStorageType.name: esaProbeStorageType
esaProbeStorageType.description: The type of storage configured for this entry.

esaProbeRowStatus.name: esaProbeRowStatus
esaProbeRowStatus.description: The status of this row. An entry MUST NOT exist in the active state unless all objects in the entry have an appropriate value, as described in the description clause for each writable object. The values of esaProbeRowStatus supported are createAndGo(4) and destroy(6). All mandatory attributes must be specified in a single SNMP SET request with esaProbeRowStatus value as createAndGo(4). Upon successful row creation, this variable has a value of active(1). The esaProbeRowStatus object may be modified if the associated instance of this object is equal to active(1).

esaProbeMultiCOSEnabled.name: esaProbeMultiCOSEnabled
esaProbeMultiCOSEnabled.description: This object is introduced for FSP150CC Release 4.3. This object is only applicable for Y.1731 and SLM-SLR Probe Protocol Types. This object can be used to specify the multiple class of services (COS) for each ESA Probe.

esaProbeSLAMonitorType.name: esaProbeSLAMonitorType
esaProbeSLAMonitorType.description: This object indicates whether the Probe is a point-to-point type or a point-to-multipoint type. Only SLM-SLR probes can be point-to-multipoint.

esaProbeCOSType.name: esaProbeCOSType
esaProbeCOSType.description: This object can be used to specify the first Class of Service associated with the Y.1731/SLM-SLR ESA Probe. In the case of a multiCOS Probe, this object has no semantics when multiple COS levels exist. This object is only valid for Y.1731/SLM-SLR ESA Probes.

esaProbeSLMMulticastMACEnabled.name: esaProbeSLMMulticastMACEnabled
esaProbeSLMMulticastMACEnabled.description: This object can be used to specify whether the SLM/SLR protocol Probe will use multicast MAC address in SLM (Synthetic Loss Measurement) messages. This object is only valid for SLM-SLR ESA Probes.

esaProbeSOAMInterval.name: esaProbeSOAMInterval
esaProbeSOAMInterval.description: This object can be used to specify the packet interval type for Y.1731 LM/DM and SLM/SLR based ESA Probes, for the first Class of Service. In the case of a multiCOS Probe, this object has no semantics when multiple COS levels exist. This attribute is applicable for Y.1731 LM/DM and SLM/SLR based probes.

esaProbeSOAMPktSize.name: esaProbeSOAMPktSize
esaProbeSOAMPktSize.description: This object can be used to specify the packet size for SLM-SLR based ESA Probes, for the first Class of Service. In the case of multiCOS Probe, this object has no semantics when multiple COS levels exist. In such cases this will return a value of 0.

esaProbeInner2VlanTagEnabled.name: esaProbeInner2VlanTagEnabled
esaProbeInner2VlanTagEnabled.description: Ability to specify whether or not to use Inner2 VLAN tag. NOTE: This attribute is not applicable to Y.1731 probes.

esaProbeInner2VlanTagEtherType.name: esaProbeInner2VlanTagEtherType
esaProbeInner2VlanTagEtherType.description: This variable allows the user to specify the monitored service's Inner2 VLAN tag Ether Type. Valid if 'esaProbeInner2VlanTagEnabled' is specified as TRUE. NOTE: This attribute is not applicable to Y.1731 probes.

esaProbeInner2VlanId.name: esaProbeInner2VlanId
esaProbeInner2VlanId.description: This variable allows the user to specify the monitored service's Inner2 VLAN tag. Valid if 'esaProbeInner2VlanTagEnabled' is specified as TRUE. NOTE: This attribute is not applicable to Y.1731 probes.

esaProbeInner2VlanPrio.name: esaProbeInner2VlanPrio
esaProbeInner2VlanPrio.description: This variable allows the user to specify the monitored service's Inner2 VLAN priority. Valid if 'esaProbeInner2VlanTagEnabled' is specified as TRUE. NOTE: This attribute is not applicable to Y.1731 probes.

esaProbeAdminState.name: esaProbeAdminState
esaProbeAdminState.description: This object represents the Administrative State of the ESA Probe. This is not externally managed.

esaProbeOperationalState.name: esaProbeOperationalState
esaProbeOperationalState.description: This object represents the Operational State of the ESA Probe.

esaProbeSecondaryState.name: esaProbeSecondaryState
esaProbeSecondaryState.description: This object represents the Secondary State of the ESA Probe.

esaProbeMacAddress.name: esaProbeMacAddress
esaProbeMacAddress.description: This attribute is applicable only for Y.1731 probes. It identifies the destination MacAddress which esa using

esaProbeAlias.name: esaProbeAlias
esaProbeAlias.description: This object allows SNMP management entities to provide an alias for an ESA Probe.

esaProbeScheduleGroupTable.name: esaProbeScheduleGroupTable
esaProbeScheduleGroupTable.description: A list of entries that allow groups of ESA Probes to be scheduled.

esaProbeScheduleGroupEntry.name: esaProbeScheduleGroupEntry
esaProbeScheduleGroupEntry.description: A row in esaProbeScheduleGroupTable. Entries are created in this table by management application action.

esaProbeScheduleGroupIndex.name: esaProbeScheduleGroupIndex
esaProbeScheduleGroupIndex.description: A unique index to distinguish the ESA Probe Schedule Group.

esaProbeScheduleGroupDescr.name: esaProbeScheduleGroupDescr
esaProbeScheduleGroupDescr.description: Description of the probe schedule group.

esaProbeScheduleGroupProbeList.name: esaProbeScheduleGroupProbeList
esaProbeScheduleGroupProbeList.description: A comma separated list of esaProbeName's, that will have the same schedule.

esaProbeScheduleGroupType.name: esaProbeScheduleGroupType
esaProbeScheduleGroupType.description: This object allows to specify whether the ESA probe group schedule is 'one-shot' or 'periodic'. A 'one-shot' schedule executes only once and then stops. A 'periodic' schedule reoccurs every 'esaProbeScheduleGroupInterval' seconds and continues until explicitly stopped.

esaProbeScheduleGroupStartTime.name: esaProbeScheduleGroupStartTime
esaProbeScheduleGroupStartTime.description: This object allows specification of the start time of the ESA Probe Group. Value of time less than current system time will equate to current time. When the system time reaches this configured time, the ESA Probe Group will be activated.

esaProbeScheduleGroupDuration.name: esaProbeScheduleGroupDuration
esaProbeScheduleGroupDuration.description: This object allows specification of the duration in 'seconds' for ESA Probe Group run. Note that a value of 4294967295 means Duration as FOREVER. FOREVER value is only applicable to schedule type oneshot. The value 4294967295 cannot be used if schedule type is periodic.

esaProbeScheduleGroupInterval.name: esaProbeScheduleGroupInterval
esaProbeScheduleGroupInterval.description: This object allows specification of the interval in 'seconds' between successive runs for ESA Probe Group. This variable is only valid if the 'esaProbeScheduleGroupType' is 'periodic'.

esaProbeScheduleGroupAction.name: esaProbeScheduleGroupAction
esaProbeScheduleGroupAction.description: This object allows to suspend/resume the ESA scheduled group.

esaProbeScheduleGroupStatus.name: esaProbeScheduleGroupStatus
esaProbeScheduleGroupStatus.description: This object indicates the current status of the ESA Probe Group.

esaProbeScheduleGroupStorageType.name: esaProbeScheduleGroupStorageType
esaProbeScheduleGroupStorageType.description: The type of storage configured for this entry.

esaProbeScheduleGroupRowStatus.name: esaProbeScheduleGroupRowStatus
esaProbeScheduleGroupRowStatus.description: The status of this row. An entry MUST NOT exist in the active state unless all objects in the entry have an appropriate value, as described in the description clause for each writable object. The values of esaProbeScheduleGroupRowStatus supported are createAndGo(4) and destroy(6). All mandatory attributes must be specified in a single SNMP SET request with esaProbeRowStatus value as createAndGo(4). Upon successful row creation, this variable has a value of active(1). The esaProbeScheduleGroupRowStatus object may be modified if the associated instance of this object is equal to active(1).

esaProbeScheduleGroupActionProbeList.name: esaProbeScheduleGroupActionProbeList
esaProbeScheduleGroupActionProbeList.description: A comma separated list of esaProbeName's, if set esaProbeScheduleGroupAction as add or remove, they will be add or remove from esaProbeScheduleGroupProbeList.

esaReflectorTable.name: esaReflectorTable
esaReflectorTable.description: A list of entries corresponding to ESA Reflectors. NOTE: There is no need to create reflectors for Y.1731 probes as the MEPs will respond by default.

esaReflectorEntry.name: esaReflectorEntry
esaReflectorEntry.description: A row in the esaReflectorTable. Entries can be created in this table by management application action.

esaReflectorIndex.name: esaReflectorIndex
esaReflectorIndex.description: A unique index to distinguish the ESA Reflector.

esaReflectorName.name: esaReflectorName
esaReflectorName.description: A unique identifier to distinguish the ESA Reflector.

esaReflectorIpAddress.name: esaReflectorIpAddress
esaReflectorIpAddress.description: This object allows specification of the Reflector's IP Address. Reflector listens for packets destined at this IP Address.

esaReflectorSubnetMask.name: esaReflectorSubnetMask
esaReflectorSubnetMask.description: This object allows specification of the Reflector's IP Subnet mask.

esaReflectorSourcePort.name: esaReflectorSourcePort
esaReflectorSourcePort.description: This object points to the Port to which the ESA Reflector is attached, i.e.on which the service to be monitored resides.

esaReflectorIpPrioMapMode.name: esaReflectorIpPrioMapMode
esaReflectorIpPrioMapMode.description: This object enables specification of Priority Mapping Mode for the ESA Reflector.

esaReflectorIpPriority.name: esaReflectorIpPriority
esaReflectorIpPriority.description: This object enables specification of Priority Value for esaReflectorPrioMapMode as priomap-tos,priomap-dscp.

esaReflectorAction.name: esaReflectorAction
esaReflectorAction.description: This object allows to suspend/resume the ESA reflector.

esaReflectorSuspended.name: esaReflectorSuspended
esaReflectorSuspended.description: This object indicates whether the ESA Reflector is active or suspended.

esaReflectorCreationTime.name: esaReflectorCreationTime
esaReflectorCreationTime.description: This object provides the creation time of the ESA Reflector.

esaReflectorStorageType.name: esaReflectorStorageType
esaReflectorStorageType.description: The type of storage configured for this entry.

esaReflectorRowStatus.name: esaReflectorRowStatus
esaReflectorRowStatus.description: The status of this row. An entry MUST NOT exist in the active state unless all objects in the entry have an appropriate value, as described in the description clause for each writable object. The values of esaReflectorRowStatus supported are createAndGo(4) and destroy(6). All mandatory attributes must be specified in a single SNMP SET request with esaReflectorRowStatus value as createAndGo(4). Upon successful row creation, this variable has a value of active(1). The esaReflectorRowStatus object may be modified if the associated instance of this object is equal to active(1).

esaReflectorDirection.name: esaReflectorDirection
esaReflectorDirection.description: This object provides the direction of the ESA Reflector.

esaReflectorAdminState.name: esaReflectorAdminState
esaReflectorAdminState.description: This object represents the Administrative State of the ESA Reflector. This is not externally managed.

esaReflectorOperationalState.name: esaReflectorOperationalState
esaReflectorOperationalState.description: This object represents the Operational State of the ESA Reflector.

esaReflectorSecondaryState.name: esaReflectorSecondaryState
esaReflectorSecondaryState.description: This object represents the Secondary State of the ESA Reflector.

esaReflectorMacAddress.name: esaReflectorMacAddress
esaReflectorMacAddress.description: This attribute is applicable only for Y.1731 probes. It identifies the destination MacAddress which esa using

esaReflectorAlias.name: esaReflectorAlias
esaReflectorAlias.description: This object allows SNMP management entities to provide an alias for an ESA Reflector.

esaProbeStatsTable.name: esaProbeStatsTable
esaProbeStatsTable.description: A collection of ESA Probe related statistics kept for a particular ESA Probe entity. These reflect the current data.

esaProbeStatsEntry.name: esaProbeStatsEntry
esaProbeStatsEntry.description: A conceptual row in the esaProbeStatsTable. An entry exists in this table for each ESA Probe.

esaProbeStatsDestinationIndex.name: esaProbeStatsDestinationIndex
esaProbeStatsDestinationIndex.description: An integer index value used to uniquely identify a destination (Reflector) Index, in a point-to-multi point SLA. For Release 4.1 GE206, this value is 1, since only point-to-point SLA is supported.

esaProbeStatsCOSIndex.name: esaProbeStatsCOSIndex
esaProbeStatsCOSIndex.description: An integer index value used to uniquely identify SLA for a specific Class of Service. For Release 4.1 GE206, this value is 1, since the COS is explicitly specified in the Probe parameters.

esaProbeStatsIndex.name: esaProbeStatsIndex
esaProbeStatsIndex.description: An arbitrary integer index value used to uniquely identify this ESA Probe statistics entry. Index 1 corresponds to current and index 2 to rollover.

esaProbeStatsIntervalType.name: esaProbeStatsIntervalType
esaProbeStatsIntervalType.description: Indicates the type of collection, i.e. whether it is current, or rollover.

esaProbeStatsCOS.name: esaProbeStatsCOS
esaProbeStatsCOS.description: The Class of Service. For Release 4.1 GE206, this value is cos-not-applicable, since multi COS SLA is not supported.

esaProbeStatsValid.name: esaProbeStatsValid
esaProbeStatsValid.description: Indicates the validity of the bin.

esaProbeStatsAction.name: esaProbeStatsAction
esaProbeStatsAction.description: Allows the Manager to clear the bin.

esaProbeStatsP2RPkts.name: esaProbeStatsP2RPkts
esaProbeStatsP2RPkts.description: The total number of Transmitted Packets in the current interval. In the case of Y.1731 probes, this reflects the number of DMRs (Delay Measurement Replies) received and this will always be the same as the esaProbeStatsR2PPkts.

esaProbeStatsP2RErredPkts.name: esaProbeStatsP2RErredPkts
esaProbeStatsP2RErredPkts.description: The total number of Packets in the current interval, for which there was a problem in transmission. This error is counted when there is a failure in packet transmission due to resource limitations (buffers). This can happen if the Probe Configuration was changed to send in a large number of packets in a time interval. NOTE: This is not applicable for Y.1731 probes.

esaProbeStatsP2RSyncErrs.name: esaProbeStatsP2RSyncErrs
esaProbeStatsP2RSyncErrs.description: The number of (time) Synchronization Errors from probe to reflector in the current interval.

esaProbeStatsP2RLostPkts.name: esaProbeStatsP2RLostPkts
esaProbeStatsP2RLostPkts.description: The number of Lost Pkts from probe to reflector in the current interval. For Y.1731 probes, these are the actual data frames lost.

esaProbeStatsR2PPkts.name: esaProbeStatsR2PPkts
esaProbeStatsR2PPkts.description: The total number of Received Packets in the current interval. In the case of Y.1731 probes, this reflects the number of DMRs (Delay Measurement Replies) received and this will always be the same as the esaProbeStatsP2RPkts.

esaProbeStatsR2PErredPkts.name: esaProbeStatsR2PErredPkts
esaProbeStatsR2PErredPkts.description: The total number of Received Packets in the current interval, which had errors such as length of received packet is less than the protocol header length, packet was received after it was marked as lost (i.e.beyond timeout). NOTE: This is not applicable for Y.1731 probes.

esaProbeStatsR2PSyncErrs.name: esaProbeStatsR2PSyncErrs
esaProbeStatsR2PSyncErrs.description: The number of (time) Synchronization Errors from reflector to probe in the current interval.

esaProbeStatsR2PLostPkts.name: esaProbeStatsR2PLostPkts
esaProbeStatsR2PLostPkts.description: The number of Lost Pkts from reflector to probe in the current interval. For Y.1731 probes, these are the actual data frames lost.

esaProbeStatsLostPkts.name: esaProbeStatsLostPkts
esaProbeStatsLostPkts.description: The total number of Lost Packets in the current interval. Packets which are not received from the reflector end beyond the configured timeout value are termed as lost. NOTE: This is not applicable for Y.1731 probes.

esaProbeStatsSeqGaps.name: esaProbeStatsSeqGaps
esaProbeStatsSeqGaps.description: The total number of sequence gaps across all packets received in the current interval. If (Received Seq Number) is greater than or equal to (Last Received Seq Number + 2)) it is termed as a sequence gap. NOTE: This is not applicable for Y.1731 probes.

esaProbeStatsOutOfSeqErrs.name: esaProbeStatsOutOfSeqErrs
esaProbeStatsOutOfSeqErrs.description: The total number of out of sequence errors across all packets received in the current interval. If (Received Seq Number) is less than or equal to (Last Received Seq Number), it is termed as out of sequence error. NOTE: This is not applicable for Y.1731 probes.

esaProbeStatsMinRoundTripDelay.name: esaProbeStatsMinRoundTripDelay
esaProbeStatsMinRoundTripDelay.description: The minimum round-trip delay(in microseconds) across all packets received in the current interval. The reflector's processing time is excluded from the value.

esaProbeStatsMaxRoundTripDelay.name: esaProbeStatsMaxRoundTripDelay
esaProbeStatsMaxRoundTripDelay.description: The maximum round-trip delay(in microseconds) across all packets received in the current interval. The reflector's processing time is excluded from the value.

esaProbeStatsAvgRoundTripDelay.name: esaProbeStatsAvgRoundTripDelay
esaProbeStatsAvgRoundTripDelay.description: The average round-trip delay(in microseconds) across all packets received in the current interval. The reflector's processing time is excluded from the value.

esaProbeStatsSumRoundTripDelay.name: esaProbeStatsSumRoundTripDelay
esaProbeStatsSumRoundTripDelay.description: The total sum of round trip delay(in microseconds) in the current interval. The reflector's processing time is excluded from the value.

esaProbeStatsSumOfSqRoundTripDelay.name: esaProbeStatsSumOfSqRoundTripDelay
esaProbeStatsSumOfSqRoundTripDelay.description: The sum of square of round trip delays in the current interval.

esaProbeStatsMinOnewayP2RDelay.name: esaProbeStatsMinOnewayP2RDelay
esaProbeStatsMinOnewayP2RDelay.description: The minimum one-way source to destination delay(in microseconds) across all packets received in the current interval.

esaProbeStatsMaxOnewayP2RDelay.name: esaProbeStatsMaxOnewayP2RDelay
esaProbeStatsMaxOnewayP2RDelay.description: The maximum one-way source to destination delay(in microseconds) across all packets received in the current interval.

esaProbeStatsAvgOnewayP2RDelay.name: esaProbeStatsAvgOnewayP2RDelay
esaProbeStatsAvgOnewayP2RDelay.description: The average one-way source to destination delay(in microseconds) across all packets received in the current interval.

esaProbeStatsSumOnewayP2RDelay.name: esaProbeStatsSumOnewayP2RDelay
esaProbeStatsSumOnewayP2RDelay.description: The total sum of one-way delay from source to destination in the current interval.

esaProbeStatsSumOfSqOnewayP2RDelay.name: esaProbeStatsSumOfSqOnewayP2RDelay
esaProbeStatsSumOfSqOnewayP2RDelay.description: The sum of square of one-way delay from source to destination in the current interval.

esaProbeStatsMinOnewayR2PDelay.name: esaProbeStatsMinOnewayR2PDelay
esaProbeStatsMinOnewayR2PDelay.description: The minimum one-way destination to source delay(in microseconds) across all packets received in the current interval.

esaProbeStatsMaxOnewayR2PDelay.name: esaProbeStatsMaxOnewayR2PDelay
esaProbeStatsMaxOnewayR2PDelay.description: The maximum one-way destination to source delay(in microseconds) across all packets received in the current interval.

esaProbeStatsAvgOnewayR2PDelay.name: esaProbeStatsAvgOnewayR2PDelay
esaProbeStatsAvgOnewayR2PDelay.description: The average one-way destination to source delay(in microseconds) across all packets received in the current interval.

esaProbeStatsY1731P2RNegLossOccurrences.name: esaProbeStatsY1731P2RNegLossOccurrences
esaProbeStatsY1731P2RNegLossOccurrences.description: This attribute is only applicable to Y.1731 probes. This is the number of occurences of negative frame loss from Source MEP (Probe) to Destination MEP (Reflector). If these counts are non-zero then there could be some kind of provisioning mismatch between the Probe MEP and Reflector MEP. Here are some scenarios this can happen: - Probe MEP is configured to count in-profile frames only and the Reflector MEP is configured to count all frames with a mismatch in value for the attribute cfmMepLmCountInProfileFrames. - Probe MEP is configured to count data frames for specific VLAN priority and the Reflector MEP is configured to count data frames for all the priorities with a mismatch in values for the attributes cfmMepLmTxCountAllPrios or cfmMepLmRxCountAllPrios. NOTE: This could possibly happen due to reasons not related to configuration such as frame reordering in the network.

Here are some scenarios this can happen: - Probe MEP is configured to count in-profile frames only and the Reflector MEP is configured to count all frames with a mismatch in value for the attribute cfmMepLmCountInProfileFrames. - Probe MEP is configured to count data frames for specific VLAN priority and the Reflector MEP is configured to count data frames for all the priorities with a mismatch in values for the attributes cfmMepLmTxCountAllPrios or cfmMepLmRxCountAllPrios. esaProbeStatsY1731P2RFrames.name: esaProbeStatsY1731P2RFrames
esaProbeStatsY1731P2RFrames.description: This attribute is only applicable to Y.1731 probes. esaProbeHistoryDestinationIndex.description: An integer index value used to uniquely identify a destination (Reflector) Index, in a point-to-multi point SLA. For Release 4.1 GE206, this value is 1, since only point-to-point SLA is supported.

esaProbeHistoryCOSIndex.name: esaProbeHistoryCOSIndex
esaProbeHistoryCOSIndex.description: An integer index value used to uniquely identify SLA for a specific Class of Service. For Release 4.1 GE206, this value is 1, since the COS is explicitly specified in the Probe parameters.

esaProbeHistoryIndex.name: esaProbeHistoryIndex
esaProbeHistoryIndex.description: An arbitrary integer index value used to uniquely identify this ESA Probe statistics history entry.

esaProbeHistoryTime.name: esaProbeHistoryTime
esaProbeHistoryTime.description: Indicates the time of history bin creation.

esaProbeHistoryValid.name: esaProbeHistoryValid
esaProbeHistoryValid.description: Indicates the validity of the bin.

esaProbeHistoryAction.name: esaProbeHistoryAction
esaProbeHistoryAction.description: Allows the Manager to clear the bin.

esaProbeHistoryCOS.name: esaProbeHistoryCOS
esaProbeHistoryCOS.description: The Class of Service. For Release 4.1 GE206, this value is cos-not-applicable, since multi COS SLA is not supported.

esaProbeHistoryP2RPkts.name: esaProbeHistoryP2RPkts
esaProbeHistoryP2RPkts.description: The total number of Transmitted Packets in the current interval. In the case of Y.1731 probes, this reflects the number of DMRs (Delay Measurement Replies) received and this will always be the same as the esaProbeHistoryR2PPkts.

esaProbeHistoryP2RErredPkts.name: esaProbeHistoryP2RErredPkts
esaProbeHistoryP2RErredPkts.description: The total number of Packets in the current interval, for which there was a problem in transmission. This error is counted when there is a failure in packet transmission due to resource limitations (buffers). This can happen if the Probe Configuration was changed to send in a large number of packets in a time interval. NOTE: This is not applicable for Y.1731 probes.

esaProbeHistoryP2RSyncErrs.name: esaProbeHistoryP2RSyncErrs
esaProbeHistoryP2RSyncErrs.description: The number of (time) Synchronization Errors from probe to reflector in the current interval.

esaProbeHistoryP2RLostPkts.name: esaProbeHistoryP2RLostPkts
esaProbeHistoryP2RLostPkts.description: The number of Lost Pkts from probe to reflector in the current interval. For Y.1731 probes, these are the actual data frames lost.

esaProbeHistoryR2PPkts.name: esaProbeHistoryR2PPkts
esaProbeHistoryR2PPkts.description: The total number of Received Packets in the current interval. In the case of Y.1731 probes, this reflects the number of DMRs (Delay Measurement Replies) received and this will always be the same as the esaProbeHistoryP2RPkts.

esaProbeHistoryR2PErredPkts.name: esaProbeHistoryR2PErredPkts
esaProbeHistoryR2PErredPkts.description: The total number of Received Packets in the current interval, which had errors such as length of received packet is less than the protocol header length, packet was received after it was marked as lost (i.e.beyond timeout). NOTE: This is not applicable for Y.1731 probes.

esaProbeHistoryR2PSyncErrs.name: esaProbeHistoryR2PSyncErrs
esaProbeHistoryR2PSyncErrs.description: The number of (time) Synchronization Errors from reflector to probe in the current interval.

esaProbeHistoryR2PLostPkts.name: esaProbeHistoryR2PLostPkts
esaProbeHistoryR2PLostPkts.description: The number of Lost Pkts from reflector to probe in the current interval. For Y.1731 probes, these are the actual data frames lost.

esaProbeHistoryLostPkts.name: esaProbeHistoryLostPkts
esaProbeHistoryLostPkts.description: The total number of Lost Packets in the current interval. Packets which are not received from the reflector end beyond the configured timeout value are termed as lost. NOTE: This is not applicable for Y.1731 probes.

esaProbeHistorySeqGaps.name: esaProbeHistorySeqGaps
esaProbeHistorySeqGaps.description: The total number of sequence gaps across all packets received in the current interval. If (Received Seq Number) is greater than or equal to (Last Received Seq Number + 2)) it is termed as a sequence gap. NOTE: This is not applicable for Y.1731 probes.

bertControlDuration.description: This object enables specification of the time in seconds for BERT. BERT will be stopped after the specified time interval is exhausted.

bertControlStream.name: bertControlStream
bertControlStream.description: This object specifies which stream should be included in the BERT execution. Value of 0 indicates that no streams is selected by bertControlStream. Non 0 value indicates the selected BERT stream.

bertControlAction.name: bertControlAction
bertControlAction.description: This object enables starting/stopping of traffic generation as well as resetting of monitored streams. This object may not be specified at configuration creation time - in this case it will take the value of `none'. This allows manager to explicitly control the start and stop of traffic generation/monitoring activity. Value of `stop' is invalid if the activity is specified but not started. Value of `start' is valid during creation time, as well as when activity is already stopped. Specification of `reset' resets the specified streams to default values, as well as clears the control specification. Get on this variable gives the most recent SNMP set specification.

bertControlTestStatus.name: bertControlTestStatus
bertControlTestStatus.description: This object reflects the current status of test set configuration entry. Upon creation, the status has a value of `initial'; the status changes to `in-progress' upon ecpaControlAction indicating `start'; the status changes to `completed' upon ecpaControlAction indicating stop, as well as when the specified test generation completes autonomously upon completion of number of frames or completion of specified time interval.
